[4] Pakistan (Khyber)
Date: Mon 17 Nov 2014
Source: The Nation Newspaper [edited]
http://nation.com.pk/national/17-Nov-2014/measles-kills-two-minors-in-khyber


Two infants have died as a result of a measles outbreak here in Pasede Khel, the remote and bordering area of tehsil Landi Kotal of the Khyber Agency, the affected family sources reported on Sunday [16 Nov 2014]. The sources said that 2 children, aged one and 3, died of measles within 2 days of onset of their illnesses.

The uncle of one of the boys said that every 3rd child in every house in Pasede Khel is suffering from measles, and the disease has turned into an epidemic. Morga, Madi Khel, Ghbargi Khel and Shegi Khel are the worst effected villages of the area, he disclosed. Routine vaccination has not been done properly, and only selective immunization has been undertaken.

According to a local parent, responsibility for treatment has been relocated to hospitals in Landi Kotal and Peshawar. Dr. Feroz Shah said: "Lack of health awareness in the community, especially among women, is the main cause of spread of the disease. When Dr. Rehman, Surgeon for the Khyber Agency, was contacted on the issue, he confirmed the occurrence of the outbreak and the 2 deaths. He stated that emergency vaccination teams had been dispatched to the area a week ago and had been carrying out vaccination in the affected area.

--
