[5] USA (Honolulu)
Date: Fri 14 Nov 2014
Source: KITV.com [edited]
http://www.kitv.com/news/New-measles-case-reported-on-Oahu/29737224


State health officials [in Hawaii] say the count of cases in this latest measles outbreak is now up to a dozen. The latest case turned up here in Honolulu. It's the 2nd adult case on Oahu this month [November 2014].

Health department [DOH] officials only learned of the cases after the test came back positive. DOH says it can't stress enough the importance of early reporting. "You need to engage us because the time is ticking to then talk to these individuals to find out who they might have been around that were infected," said Dr. Sarah Park of the state DOH.

This 2nd case also had no history of travel, so right now, it can't be linked to the cases on the neighboring islands. Park says one of the Oahu cases may have been in contact with more than 90 people. She advises people to make sure they have been vaccinated and that some may need 2 shots.

--
